#Boolean variable 
"""

*****...................................Important note ..........................................
in boolean built in function 0 is false and 1 is true but if we give input as int ....and if we give input as string than boolean function take 0 as string and boolean function retrurn as True.

In boolean function:
In fact, there are not many values that evaluate to False, except empty values, such as (), [], {}, "", the number 0, and the value None. And of course the value False evaluates to False.

Almost any value is evaluated to True if it has some sort of content.

Any string is True, except empty strings.

Any number is True, except 0.

Any list, tuple, set, and dictionary are True, except empty ones.

...................................Important note ..........................................
"""
#...................................Code ..........................................

n = int(input("How Many Row You Want To Print \n"))
print("In which data type of you want to type for boolean \n string or int ")
k=input("Enter Strin or Int \n")
if (k=="Strin"):
    b=input("Enter string \n")
elif (k=="Int"):
    b= int(input("Enter the number 0 or 1 \n"))
a = bool(b)
i=n
if a == False:
    while(i>0):
        for k in range(0,i):
             print("*",end="")
        i -= 1
        print("")
elif a == True:
    while(i>0):
        for k in range(i,n+1):
             print("*",end="")
        i -= 1
        print("")

